23/09/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi called for the establishment of a strict control system in the judiciary Tuesday (September 22nd). 
Speaking to the High Justice Council, Topi urged its members and the Ministry of Justice to closely monitor the work of courts handling particularly sensitive cases. 
"Transparency in the verification and the overall process is very much needed in order to be fair to the public and the citizens," said Topi, citing the protracted nature of some cases. 
(Balkan Web, Shekulli, Telegrafi, Top News - 22/09/09)
